# Commit Message Guidelines

When generating commit messages, follow the Conventional Commits specification:

Format: `<type>(<scope>): <subject>`

Types:
- feat: A new feature
- fix: A bug fix
- docs: Documentation changes
- style: Code style changes (formatting, no code change)
- refactor: Code refactoring
- perf: Performance improvements
- test: Adding or updating tests
- build: Build system or dependencies
- ci: CI configuration changes
- chore: Other changes

Scopes (optional):
- web: Web application (Next.js)
- api: API application (NestJS)
- shared-ui: Shared UI library
- shared-data-access: Shared data access library

Rules:
- Use lowercase for type and scope
- Subject should be imperative mood ("add" not "added")
- No period at the end of subject
- Keep subject under 72 characters

Examples:
- feat(web): add user authentication flow
- fix(api): resolve token expiration issue
- docs: update contributing guidelines
- chore: update dependencies

